  "response_text": "A warm, yellow-lit bedroom appears with several people crowded together in bed under patterned covers and floral pillows. In the foreground, a Black adult man lies on his back wearing a dark pajama top covered with large pale dots. He stirs awake, raises one arm toward his face, and begins a huge yawn. His eyes squeeze shut and his mouth opens wider and wider, filling the view as he lies against a pillow with large reddish-orange flowers. Behind him, other sleepers are partly visible among plaid bedding and pillows.\n\nThe view shifts to a Black adult woman lying on the same bed, wearing striped pajamas. She is on her back with short, curly dark hair spread against a floral pillow. She also yawns broadly, her mouth open wide and her head tipped back. As she finishes, a very large dark dog’s head comes into view at the left side of the bed, close to the pillows. The dog has a long black muzzle, visible teeth, and a tan or light-colored body or covering below its head. Its mouth opens in a big panting or yawning expression, showing its teeth and tongue area, while the woman lies beside it with her face turned upward.\n\nThe scene changes to a bright, spotless bathroom with a white toilet centered against glossy white rectangular wall tiles. A toilet paper roll is mounted on the wall to the left, and a pale towel hangs to the right. The toilet is clean and gleaming, with soft pinkish-white lighting.\n\nA product package fills the view: a green box with the bold Clorox Bleach logo at the top in dark blue letters inside the familiar red-and-white diamond shape. A diagonal red stripe runs across the lower green section, with small text that appears to identify it as an automatic toilet cleaner. A picture of a toilet tank appears near the bottom. In front of the box, a round white tablet appears and moves across the package like a thick, flat mint, emphasizing its tablet shape.\n\nA demonstration follows on a plain, studio-like surface. A hand tilts a white Clorox bleach bottle with the rainbow-striped Clorox label, pouring clear liquid onto a small white round tablet standing on the surface. The liquid stream runs from the bottle mouth onto the tablet, visually linking the tablet with bleach.\n\nBack in the bathroom, a hand holds a small white packet with the Clorox logo above the open area of the toilet tank. The packet is tipped, and a white round tablet slides out and drops down into the tank. The same hand then reaches to the chrome flush handle on the side of the toilet tank and presses it downward. The toilet is shown from the front as the flush begins; then the seat and lid rise, revealing the open bowl.\n\nThe product box returns, again showing the green Clorox Bleach Automatic Toilet Cleaner package with the round white tablet hovering in front of it. The tablet glides across the front of the box and settles near the pictured toilet tank on the package. Finally, the bathroom toilet appears clean and open, with the product box standing on the floor or low surface to the left of the toilet bowl, visually pairing the fresh-looking toilet with the Clorox Automatic Toilet Cleaner package.",
